                     <interp inst="t18310630-143-person1055" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the 1st of June I was in Newgate-street, about half-past ten o'clock - I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket, at the corner of Butcherhall-lane; he dropped it: the prosecutor turned round, and picked it up; the prisoner then ran down the lane, and I after him, crying Stop thief! he stopped in about two minutes, and I took hold of him - I had not lost sight of him.</p>
